<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-07-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="434" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Draper</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-07-24"><hi rend="italic">July 24,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Inform minister for foreign affairs that the governor of Louisiana is
                            investigating the alleged lynching of persons born in Italy, and that
                            this Government will take all legal steps to secure justice which the
                            facts may warrant.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>